### 341.

The width of the shoulders is 1/4 of the whole. From the joint of the
shoulder to the hand is 1/3, from the parting of the lips to below the
shoulder-blade is one foot.

The greatest thickness of a man from the breast to the spine is one 8th
of his height and is equal to the space between the bottom of the chin
and the top of the head.

The greatest width is at the shoulders and goes 4.

